cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper deals with a learning-based approach for motion estimation in interventional C-arm cone-beam computed tomography (CBCT) and extends it with a CBCT consistency constraint. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques for image reconstruction and machine learning (ML) for motion estimation. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves deep learning (DL) techniques, which fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
